The latest technology legend project, Inrupt, is a company based on Berners-Lee's open-source platform Solid.
With Solid, users can choose where their data is stored and who gets access to what information.
In an exclusive interview with Fast Company, Berners-Lee gave the best idea that the intention behind Inrupt was the "world domination".
"We must now become active," he said on startup.
"It's a historic moment."
The app uses Solid's technology so users can create their own personal online data storage or a POD.
It can contain contact lists, task lists, a calendar, a music library, as well as other tools for the private and corporate sector.
Similar to Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack and Spotify, all content is available in one browser and at the same time.
The special feature of the personal online data storage is that the user can decide by himself who can access which data.
The Company refers to this concept as personal strengthening and development through data.
According to the CEO of the company John Bruce, the idea behind Inrupt is that the company uses resources, processes and related capabilities so that Solid is available to everyone.
The company currently includes Berners-Lee, Bruce, some developers who have been hired to work on this project, as well as a community of voluntary programmers. Furthermore, a security platform acquired by IBM is used.
From the beginning of this week, technology developers worldwide can create their own decentralised apps with the tools available on the Inrupt website.
Berners-Lee announced that he and his team will not exchange with Facebook and Google on whether a comprehensive change is to be made, in which their entire business models will be completely remodelled overnight.
"We do not ask for their permission."
In a paper on medium published on Saturday, Berners-Lee wrote that Inrupt has the task of providing commercial energy generation and an ecosystem to protect the integrity and quality of the new, solid-based web.
In 1994, Berners-Lee redesigned the Internet when he founded the World Wide Web Consortium at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.
Over the past few months Berners-Lee has played a major role in the debate on net neutrality.
Even with the launch of Inrupt, Berners-Lee remains the founder and director of the World Wide Web Consortium, the Web Foundation and the Open Data Institute.
"I am extremely confident about this new era of the web," he added.
Priest Bernard Vann, carrier of the Victoria Cross in World War I, was honored
The only clergyman of the Church of England, who was awarded the Victoria Cross during World War I, was honored in his hometown 100 years later.
Lieutenant Colonel and Priest Bernard Vann won the award due to his commitment to attacking Bellenglise and Lehaucourt on 29 September 1918.
However, four days later he was killed by a sniper and never learned that he had won the highest British war award.
His two grandchildren revealed a memorial stone on Sunday at a parade in Rushden, Northamptonshire.
One of the grandsons, Michael Vann, said that this act is full of symbolic power, as the memorial stone was revealed exactly 100 years after the heroic act for which his grandfather was awarded.
According to The London Gazette, Lieutenant Colonel Vann led his battalion over the Canal de Saint-Quentin on September 29, 1918, through dense fog and violent fires of field guns and machine guns.
Later he pushed forward to the fire line and led the line forward with the "greatest bravery" before he rushed ahead with a field weapon in the single entrance and shut down three of the military units.
Lieutenant Colonel Vann was shot by a German sniper on October 4, 1918, just over a month before the end of the war.
Michael Vann, 72, said that the actions of his grandfather were something he could never do, and at the same time something that makes you humble.
Together with his brother, Dr. James Vann, he laid down a wreath after the parade under the direction of the Brentwood Imperial Youth Band.
Michael Vann stated that he felt very honored to be able to participate in the parade, adding that the bravery of a real hero became visible especially through the support of many people.
